<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Street fighting between rival
groups near the southern town of Uitenhage left at least five black
men dead and seven seriously injured, police reported today.
   Police said the battle Thursday was part of an ongoing feud
between supporters of the United Democratic Front, a nationwide
anti-apartheid coalition, and a group of ``Africanists.''
   Most Africanists are aligned with the outlawed Pan Africanist
Congress, which favors black self-reliance in the quest of
political rights as opposed to the Front's multiracial approach.
