stabbed or suffered blows to the head during two hours of fighting
in Kwanobuhle, a township outside Uitenhage, police said.
   The two groups have fought sporadically for political control of
the area since 1987, according to the independent South Africa
Press Association.
   The Front also is involved in a power struggle in Natal
Province, where fighting with Inkatha, a relatively conservative
Zulu organization, has left about 2,500 people dead over the past
three years.
