future economic activity edged up 0.1 percent in November, a tiny
increase seen by many analysts as evidence that growth in 1990 will
be modest at best.
   The Commerce Department said Friday the small rise in its Index
of Leading Economic Indicators followed a revised 0.3 percent
decline in October.
   For most of the year, the leading index has been flashing
signals that the U.S. economy was headed for a rather dramatic
slowdown in growth and analysts said the weak November showing did
not change that picture.
